Source: ILO calculations based on ILOSTAT and ILO, Trends Econometric Models
FOOTNOTES: The working poverty rate, part and parcel of this indicator, is calculated as the percentage of employed persons living on less than US$1.90 per day. The working age population used comprises persons aged 15 and above. Adults refer to persons aged 25 and above, and the youth refers to persons aged 15 to 24 inclusive. Unfortunately, at this stage, reliable estimates on working poverty in developed regions are not available.

FOOTNOTES: The working poverty rate, part and parcel of this indicator, is calculated as the percentage of employed persons living on less than US$1.90 per day. The working age population used comprises persons aged 15 and above. Adults refer to persons aged 25 and above, and the youth refers to persons aged 15 to 24 inclusive. Unfortunately, at this stage, reliable estimates on working poverty in developed regions are not available.

FOOTNOTES: The working poverty rate, part and parcel of this indicator, is calculated as the percentage of employed persons living on less than US$1.90 per day. The working age population used comprises persons aged 15 and above. Adults refer to persons aged 25 and above, and the youth refers to persons aged 15 to 24 inclusive. Unfortunately, at this stage, reliable estimates on working poverty in developed regions are not available.

FOOTNOTES: The working poverty rate, part and parcel of this indicator, is calculated as the percentage of employed persons living on less than US$1.90 per day. The working age population used comprises persons aged 15 and above. Adults refer to persons aged 25 and above, and the youth refers to persons aged 15 to 24 inclusive. Unfortunately, at this stage, reliable estimates on working poverty in developed regions are not available.

FOOTNOTES: The working poverty rate, part and parcel of this indicator, is calculated as the percentage of employed persons living on less than US$1.90 per day. The working age population used comprises persons aged 15 and above. Adults refer to persons aged 25 and above, and the youth refers to persons aged 15 to 24 inclusive. Unfortunately, at this stage, reliable estimates on working poverty in developed regions are not available.

FOOTNOTES: The working poverty rate, part and parcel of this indicator, is calculated as the percentage of employed persons living on less than US$1.90 per day. The working age population used comprises persons aged 15 and above. Adults refer to persons aged 25 and above, and the youth refers to persons aged 15 to 24 inclusive. Unfortunately, at this stage, reliable estimates on working poverty in developed regions are not available.

FOOTNOTES: The working poverty rate, part and parcel of this indicator, is calculated as the percentage of employed persons living on less than US$1.90 per day. The working age population used comprises persons aged 15 and above. Adults refer to persons aged 25 and above, and the youth refers to persons aged 15 to 24 inclusive. Unfortunately, at this stage, reliable estimates on working poverty in developed regions are not available.

Unfortunately, at this stage, reliable estimates on working poverty in developed regions are not available.

FOOTNOTES: The working poverty rate, part and parcel of this indicator, is calculated as the percentage of employed persons living on less than US$1.90 per day. The working age population used comprises persons aged 15 and above. Adults refer to persons aged 25 and above, and the youth refers to persons aged 15 to 24 inclusive. Unfortunately, at this stage, reliable estimates on working poverty in developed regions are not available.

FOOTNOTES: The working poverty rate, part and parcel of this indicator, is calculated as the percentage of employed persons living on less than US$1.90 per day. The working age population used comprises persons aged 15 and above. Adults refer to persons aged 25 and above, and the youth refers to persons aged 15 to 24 inclusive. Unfortunately, at this stage, reliable estimates on working poverty in developed regions are not available.

The working age population used comprises persons aged 15 and above. Adults refer to persons aged 25 and above, and the youth refers to persons aged 15 to 24 inclusive. Unfortunately, at this stage, reliable estimates on working poverty in developed regions are not available.
